    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so r u saying the problem wasnt the intervention itself, but just how it was handled later? it feels like ur putting all the blame on \"strategic incompetence\" rather than questioning if the intervention should have happened in the first place. wouldn't a realist argue that if you can't guarantee stability, the whole mission is a failure from the start, regardless of the \"tactical\" wins?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
